The parks under survey were Hampden Park, Whitley Road and Roselands Recreation Grounds, Gildredge Park (inc. Manor Gardens), Hartfield Square {Treasure Island} and{Princes Park.}
Treasure Island is a commercially run{ {adventure playground}, while the others are local amenities. They all have open spaces, gardens and, excepting Hartfield Square, play areas for children with swings, slides, roundabouts, etc.
All the parks, except Hartfield and the recreation grounds, have ponds, pools or streams. All have many trees with squirrels and birds readily observed. Gildredge Park has a very small zoo, an {art gallery} and { {museum}while all the parks, except Hartfield, have {sports provision.}
